                            <comment id="17288383" author="mkl" created="Mon, 22 Feb 2021 13:36:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Adobe Reader also displays an error dialog when opening the PDF and displays only an empty page and broken comments.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looking at the PDF the cross references are mostly incorrect, the table position is incorrect, ... that PDF is broken.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Probably one could replace the &lt;tt&gt;ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException&lt;/tt&gt; by a &lt;tt&gt;BrokenPdfException&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17288488" author="jira-bot" created="Mon, 22 Feb 2021 17:11:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1886806 from Tilman Hausherr in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1886806&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1886806&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-5104&quot; title=&quot;ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException in isOwnerPassword&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-5104&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-5104&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: avoid ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17288489" author="jira-bot" created="Mon, 22 Feb 2021 17:11:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1886807 from Tilman Hausherr in branch &apos;pdfbox/branches/2.0&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1886807&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1886807&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-5104&quot; title=&quot;ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException in isOwnerPassword&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-5104&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-5104&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: avoid ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17288490" author="tilman" created="Mon, 22 Feb 2021 17:13:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mkl&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mkl&quot;&gt;mkl&lt;/a&gt; I&apos;m just returning an IOException. Don&apos;t want to create a new exception, this would mean more code changes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17288491" author="tilman" created="Mon, 22 Feb 2021 17:13:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for reporting!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17288941" author="mkl" created="Tue, 23 Feb 2021 08:40:13 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m just returning an IOException. Don&apos;t want to create a new exception, this would mean more code changes.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Well, the &lt;tt&gt;BrokenPdfException&lt;/tt&gt; I mentioned was not really meant seriously. While it would of course be nice to have an indication that an exception implies that the PDF itself is broken and not some generic IO problem, having such an indication in just one location would not help much.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
